By my opinion we should use Rest/Mvc controller layer for following:

1) Parameters validation

2) Mapping incoming parameters(`ProductRequest`) into service model (`Product`)

3) Call services with service model

4) Return result or error

So in your case you should map `ProductRequest` to Product and path `Product` to the service. You can find one of the classic sample in this article: [DTO Conversion][1]:

    @RequestMapping(value = &quot;/{id}&quot;, method = RequestMethod.PUT)
    @ResponseStatus(HttpStatus.OK)
    public void updatePost(@RequestBody PostDto postDto) {
        Post post = convertToEntity(postDto);
        postService.updatePost(post);
    }

Also it is rule of thumb keep controller layer as thin as possible.


  [1]: https://www.baeldung.com/entity-to-and-from-dto-for-a-java-spring-application

