As you state yourself, you are doing the opposite of what you want. In addition, MongoDB returns ids as `ObjectId` instead of `string`, so equality check will always return `false`. If both objects are `ObjectId`, you should use the [`.equals` method](https://mongodb.github.io/node-mongodb-native/api-bson-generated/objectid.html#equals):

```ts
// If user has not the required role, throw a 401
if (!user.rol_id.equals(rolModel._id)) {
